data.enText: to give sth to sb or make it available for them to use

data.chText: 这家医院承诺要提供最好的医疗服务。
data.enText: The hospital has a commitment to provide the best possible medical care.

data.chText: 我们来这里是为公众服务。
data.enText: We are here to provide a service for the public.

data.chText: 我们来这里是为公众服务。
data.enText: We are here to provide the public with a service.

data.chText: 请在留出的空白处答题。
data.enText: Please answer questions in the space provided.

data.chText: 人们没有指望这个报告会提供什么答案。
data.enText: The report was not expected to provide any answers.
to state that sth will or must happen

data.chText: 最后一节规定，此后为公司创作的一切作品均为该公司所有。
data.enText: The final section provides that any work produced for the company is thereafter owned by the company.

to make preparations to deal with sth that might happen in the future

data.chText: 作出规定；使有据可依；使可以做
data.enText: to make it possible for sth to be done

data.chText: 法律规定，对嫌疑恐怖分子最多可拘留七天。
data.enText: The legislation provides for the detention of suspected terrorists for up to seven days.

simple_means.memory_skill: pro 在前 + vid 看 + e → 提前看好 → 预备

ex.enText: The manager offered him a cigarette.

ex.chText: 他给她提供了一份好工作，但她拒绝了。
ex.enText: He offered her a good job, but she turned it down.

synonyms.bx: 指主动给予帮助等，对方可以接受也可以拒绝。

ex.chText: 这房间可以看到迷人的海景。
ex.enText: The room affords a fascinating sea view.

ex.chText: 这给了他与外国的同龄人交流的机会。
ex.enText: It afforded him the opportunity to communicate with his foreign peers.

synonyms.bx: 多指提供抽象的东西，可后接双宾语。

ex.chText: 这些新的发现是否会提供更多与案件有关的线索？
ex.enText: Will these new finds furnish more clues surrounding the case?

ex.chText: 他得到了一份当地经销商的名单。
ex.enText: He was furnished with a list of local dealers.

synonyms.bx: 既可指提供抽象的东西，又可指提供具体的东西。

ex.chText: 这家餐厅为客人提供免费甜点。
ex.enText: The restaurant provides free desserts for guests.

ex.chText: 他们已给我提供了所需要的一切。
ex.enText: They have already provided me with everything I need.

ex.chText: 孩子们有良好的衣食供应。
ex.enText: The kids are provided with good food and clothing.

ex.chText: 当局有义务为老年人提供住所。
ex.enText: It is the duty of the authorities to provide homes for the old.

synonyms.bx: 指为某人提供需要或有用的东西，多用于 provide sth for sb 和provide sb with sth 结构中。

ex.chText: 这个项目所用的钢材由一家国际公司提供。
ex.enText: Steel for this project was supplied by an international company.

ex.chText: 他们因为向街头小贩提供假药而被捕。
ex.enText: They were arrested for supplying counterfeit medicine to street vendors.

ex.chText: 我们给附近的5个城镇提供电力。
ex.enText: We supply power to the five nearby towns.

synonyms.bx: 尤指长时间地定期供应所需或想要之物，多用于 supply sb with sth 和 supply sth to sb 结构中。

trans: 为…做准备；为…事先安排妥当

example: provide for the proper care of the passengers on the cruise ship

tr: determine (what is to happen in certain contingencies), especially by including a proviso condition or stipulation
example: The will provides that each child should receive half of the money
The Constitution provides for the right to free speech

tr: give what is desired or needed, especially support, food or sustenance
example: The hostess provided lunch for all the guests
He provides for his large family by working three jobs
Women nowadays not only take care of the household but also bring home the bacon

tr: give something useful or necessary to
example: We provided the room with an electrical heater

tr: make a possibility or provide opportunity for
permit to be attainable or cause to remain
example: This leaves no room for improvement
The evidence allows only one conclusion
leave lots of time for the trip
This procedure provides for lots of leeway

value.def: If you provide something that someone needs or wants, or if you provide them with it, you give it to them or make it available to them.

example.ex: I'll be glad to provide a copy of this...
example.tran: 我很愿意提供它的一个副本。

example.ex: They would not provide any details...
example.tran: 他们不愿提供任何细节。

example.ex: The government was not in a position to provide them with food.
example.tran: 政府不可能给他们提供食物。

example.ex: They remain the main providers of sports facilities.
example.tran: 他们仍然是体育设施的主要提供商。

value.def: If a law or agreement provides that something will happen, it states that it will happen.

example.ex: The treaty provides that, by the end of the century, the United States must have removed its bases...
example.tran: 条约规定，到本世纪末，美国必须撤除其基地。

example.ex: The Act provides that only the parents of a child have a responsibility for that child's financial support.
example.tran: 法令规定只有孩子的父母才有责任为孩子提供经济支持。

trans: 赡养；供养；为…做准备；为…事先安排妥当；（法律、条约）规定，允许

partsOfSpeech.dec: ad 做… + vis 看 + e → 使〔别人〕看到 → 劝告
ad 做… + vis 看 + ory …的 → 劝告的
en 使… + vis 看 + age 表行为 → 看 → 想象
e 出 + vid 看 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 证据
e 出 + vid 看 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 看出来了 → 明显的
im 不 + provident 深谋远虑的 → 没有远见的，有钱就花 → 浪费的
in 使… + vid 看 + ious …的 → 让人看 →〔易〕招嫉妒的
pre 预先 + vis 看 + e → 预先看 → 预知
pro 在前 + vid 看 + e → 提前看好 → 预备
pro 向前 + vid 看 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 向前看的 → 有远见的 → 深谋远虑的
pro 向前 + vision 眼界 + al …的 → 眼前的 → 临时的
re 一再 + vis 看 + e → 一看再看 → 一改再改 → 修正
re 一再 + vis 看 + ion，revise 的名词 → 修正；校订本
super 上 + vis 看 + e → 在上面看 → 监督
vis 看 + ible 可…的 → 可见的
vis 看 + ion 表名词 → 视力；眼界
vision 视力；眼界 + ary …的 → 幻想的
vis 看 + ual 有…性质的 → 视力的
visual 视力的 + ize …化 → 使〔大家〕看到 → 使具体化
de 加强 + vis 分开 + e → 由古义“分开”转化而来
di 二 + vid 分开 + e → 一分为二 → 分开
di 二，两 + vis 分开 + ion 表名词 → 分开
di 二，两 + vid 分开 + end 表抽象名词 → 一变二，二变多 → 股息
in 不 + di 二，两 + vid 分开 + ual 有…性质的 → 不能分开的 → 个人的
